exo 200 page 1 exo 200 russell neilson for the exo collaboration abstract the enriched xenon observatory exo is a series of experiments designed to search for the neutrinoless double beta decay of xenon 136 the first exo experiment known as exo 200 is nearing completion with data taking expected in 2008 the centerpiece of exo 200 is a liquid xenon tpc containing 200 kg of xenon enriched to 80 in xenon 136 making it by far the largest double beta decay experiment ever attempted the cryogenics and fluid handling systems for exo 200 were commissioned at stanford university in the spring of 2007 and the experiment is currently being installed in its underground location at the wipp facility in carlsbad new mexico
